explanation: This solution iterates over each pattern in the patterns vector and uses the find method of the string class to check if the pattern exists as a substring in the word. If it does, it increments a count variable. The time complexity is O(n*m*k) because in the worst case, we are searching for each pattern of length m in the word of length k, and there are n patterns.

